      action: "Binds to synaptic vesicle protein 2A (SV2A) in presynaptic terminals, modulating neurotransmitter release by reducing the readily releasable pool of synaptic vesicles; this reduces excessive excitatory neurotransmission without directly affecting GABA or glutamate receptors; also inhibits N-type calcium channels and reverses the effects of zinc and beta-carbolines on GABA-A and glycine receptors; provides broad-spectrum antiseizure activity effective against both focal and generalized seizure types",
      sideEffects: "Behavioral/psychiatric effects ('Keppra rage' -- irritability, agitation, depression, psychotic symptoms in ~10-15% of patients; more common in patients with pre-existing psychiatric conditions), somnolence/fatigue, dizziness, headache; rarely: suicidal ideation (FDA black box warning for all ASMs)",
